== 罗马統治时代 ==
[[File:Spain_Andalusia_Cordoba_BW_2015-10-27_12-15-09.jpg|thumb]]地区留存的罗马时期的桥梁]]
{{main|西班牙 (罗马行省)}}
在罗马共和国晚期，其治下的伊比利亚半岛被分为[[远西班牙|远西班牙]]和[[近西班牙|近西班牙]]；而在[[罗马帝国|罗马帝国]]时期，伊比利亚半岛则被划分为东北部的[[塔拉哥那|塔拉哥那]]、南部的[[贝提卡|贝提卡]]（大致相当于今日的[[安达卢西亚|安达卢西亚]]）和西南部的[[卢西塔尼亚|卢西塔尼亚]]（相当于今日的[[葡萄牙|葡萄牙]]）。

凯尔特人和伊比利亚人都被不同程度的[[罗马化|罗马化]]，<ref>The ''[[latifundia|latifundia]]'' (sing., ''latifundium''), large estates controlled by the aristocracy, were superimposed on the existing Iberian landholding system.</ref> 当地的首领也被吸收进罗马的贵族阶层。<ref name="country">{{cite web |last=Rinehart |first=Robert |coauthors=Seeley, Jo Ann Browning |title=A Country Study: Spain - Hispania |publisher=Library of Congress Country Series |year=1998 |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/estoc.html |accessdate=2008-08-09 |archive-date=2012-05-29 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120529143120/lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/estoc.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

罗马人发展原有的城市，如[[塔拉戈纳|塔拉戈纳]]，同时又兴建一批城市，如[[萨拉戈萨|萨拉戈萨]]、[[梅里达|梅里达]]、[[巴伦西亚|巴伦西亚]]、[[莱昂|莱昂]]和[[巴达霍斯|巴达霍斯]]等。<ref>The Roman provinces of Hispania included ''Provincia Hispania Ulterior Baetica ([[Hispania_Baetica|Hispania Baetica]])'', whose capital was [[Córdoba,_Spain|Corduba, presently Córdoba]], ''Provincia Hispania Ulterior Lusitania'' ([[Hispania_Lusitania|Hispania Lusitania]]), whose capital was Emerita Augusta (now [[Mérida,_Spain|Mérida]]), ''Provincia Hispania Citerior'', whose capital was [[Tarraco|Tarraco]] (Tarragona), ''Provincia Hispania Nova'', whose capital was [[Tingis|Tingis]] (Tánger in present Morocco), ''Provincia Hispania Nova Citerior'' and ''Asturiae-Calleciae'' (these latter two provinces were created and then dissolved in the 3rd century CE).</ref> 在罗马统治下，半岛的经济得到快速发展。伊比利亚半岛为罗马提供[[粮食|粮食]]、[[橄榄油|橄榄油]]、[[葡萄酒|葡萄酒]]和[[金属|金属]]。[[图拉真|图拉真]]、[[哈德良|哈德良]]和[[狄奥多西一世|狄奥多西一世]]3位[[罗马皇帝|罗马皇帝]]、[[哲学家|哲学家]][[塞内卡|塞内卡]]、诗人[[马蒂阿尔|马蒂阿尔]]、[[昆提利安|昆提良]]和[[卢肯|卢肯]]都出生于西班牙。[[西班牙主教|西班牙主教]]从306年开始在[[埃尔韦拉|埃尔韦拉]]（古西班牙城市，即今日的[[格拉纳达|格拉纳达]]）[[驻节|驻节]]。

公元5世纪，随着罗马帝国的衰亡，第一批[[日耳曼部落|日耳曼部落]]入侵伊比利亚半岛。<ref>{{cite web
 |last         = Payne
 |first        = Stanley G.
 |title        = A History of Spain and Portugal; Ch. 1 Ancient Hispania
 |publisher    = The Library of Iberian Resources Online
 |year         = 1973
 |url          = http://libro.uca.edu/payne1/spainport1.htm
